explain_training_effectiveness: Training on how to use the GVault interface (web-based, interactive, how-to sessions) was very helpful. Reading the SOPs and BEDs--the only information about processes-- was not. These are for reference and not for building understanding of processes and their relationship to procedures that are complex and conditional. I felt that I gained no training of the over-reaching principles of Gilead's documentation and its management, i.e, who are the audiences, what is the purpose of an SOP, a WRK vs. a BED, etc., in the general scheme of the system. Given that I'm speaking from the perspective of a fulltime document writer rather than a developer who must only update existing documents, and there may be little demand to justify such training. Criticisms aside, I think Gilead has one of the best document management systems I've seen.
